					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13704800#post-4769793</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13704800/scp-2754#post-4769793</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Sep 2020 23:19:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Grigori Karpin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558017</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So I would like to explain my downvote. First, the dialogue is very rough and could be polished into a more believable fashion. Second, I just don't feel the emotional connection to these events. Something about the way the information is revealed made me guess almost immediately this would be about someone mourning a loved one and then there would be heart warming moment&#8230; it just, for me, misses the mark when compared to my experiences with close, personal losses.</p> <p>I hope you don't think less of me for being negative on your piece :( but I didn't want to merely downvote without explaining.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
